261
00:15:13.800 --> 00:15:15.920
I bring him clients from time to time.

262
00:15:16.520 --> 00:15:17.400
It's good money.

263
00:15:17.480 --> 00:15:18.800
Want me to rope you in?

264
00:15:19.640 --> 00:15:20.800
What do you say?

265
00:15:21.520 --> 00:15:24.520
Sometimes you have to let go
or you'll go mental.

266
00:15:26.440 --> 00:15:28.920
Are you responsible
for the murder of Felicja Turczyk?

267
00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:30.560
[angry breathing]

268
00:15:30.640 --> 00:15:33.040
I may've fucked her.
but I damn well didn't kill her.

269
00:15:33.120 --> 00:15:34.000
[angry breathing]

270
00:15:34.080 --> 00:15:35.520
What do you want? Money?

271
00:15:37.480 --> 00:15:39.880
-All I want is to find her killer.
-[heavy breathing]

272
00:15:40.560 --> 00:15:42.440
Wróblewski doesn't suit you?

273
00:15:43.400 --> 00:15:46.000
Maybe he's the one who sent those photos.

274
00:15:46.080 --> 00:15:48.560
He did the same thing to Denar.
It's his M.O.

275
00:15:48.640 --> 00:15:51.240
It was anonymous.
I have no clue who sent them.

276
00:15:52.440 --> 00:15:55.000
Seems like someone's got it out
for us cops.

277
00:15:55.760 --> 00:15:58.040
Who would dare work against
the state police force?

278
00:15:58.120 --> 00:16:00.680
Someone with quite
a bit of evidence on their side.

279
00:16:00.760 --> 00:16:03.920
Evidence that helps Wróblewski.
I'm telling you. he's our murderer.

280
00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:05.760
That'll never hold up in court of law.

281
00:16:05.840 --> 00:16:06.800
Hey!

282
00:16:07.440 --> 00:16:09.720
[pants] You better can it.
I'm warning you.

283
00:16:09.800 --> 00:16:11.520
This is my case. you understand?

284
00:16:11.600 --> 00:16:13.120
[heavy breathing]

285
00:16:21.320 --> 00:16:23.920
Some might say it's time to step aside.

286
00:16:27.440 --> 00:16:29.160
[car window thumping]

287
00:16:32.040 --> 00:16:32.880
[door opens]

288
00:16:43.280 --> 00:16:46.200
King. how come
you left me hanging for so long?

289
00:16:46.680 --> 00:16:48.280
I was on holiday in Capri.

290
00:16:48.600 --> 00:16:50.760
But now I'm completely at your disposal.

291
00:16:51.160 --> 00:16:52.320
How have you been?

292
00:16:52.840 --> 00:16:54.880
I'm actually doing very well.

293
00:16:54.960 --> 00:16:56.240
I owe that to you.

294
00:16:56.320 --> 00:16:57.840
I knew you'd find happiness.

295
00:16:57.920 --> 00:16:58.760
Mm.

296
00:16:58.840 --> 00:17:01.840
-And you?
-Oh. I believe you know why I'm calling.

297
00:17:01.920 --> 00:17:05.680
Mr. Wróblewski's loan application.
secured by his villa.

298
00:17:05.760 --> 00:17:07.640
has been denied. it would seem.

299
00:17:08.079 --> 00:17:09.760
Because of his arrest?

300
00:17:09.839 --> 00:17:11.680
The house hasn't lost its market value.

301
00:17:12.640 --> 00:17:15.960
I highly doubt that sum would cover
all of his debts anyway.

302
00:17:16.040 --> 00:17:18.560
Unless you have other assets
you can leverage.

303
00:17:18.880 --> 00:17:21.920
Any possible way you could get them
to maybe reconsider?

304
00:17:23.280 --> 00:17:24.960
Look. this isn't financial.

305
00:17:25.040 --> 00:17:26.359
It's political.

306
00:17:27.160 --> 00:17:31.440
Bogumil Makowiecki is well-known
for deliberately freezing funds

307
00:17:31.520 --> 00:17:34.080
to papers he later sells
below market value.

308
00:17:34.840 --> 00:17:36.680
What is it's market value?

309
00:17:36.760 --> 00:17:38.800
I don't know the paper's situation.

310
00:17:38.880 --> 00:17:41.120
But I would recommend you not cross him.

311
00:17:41.760 --> 00:17:45.400
Unless you know someone with more pull
than I have who can help you out.

312
00:17:47.000 --> 00:17:48.200
Thanks for the tip.

313
00:18:15.320 --> 00:18:17.840
[maid] Ms. Helena! [panting]
Ms. Helena! [panting]

314
00:18:17.920 --> 00:18:19.440
Yes. I'll be ready in a moment.

315
00:18:19.520 --> 00:18:22.360
-The taxi can wait.
-You should probably come downstairs.

316
00:18:22.840 --> 00:18:24.040
[man] Helena!

317
00:18:24.800 --> 00:18:26.080
Helena!

318
00:18:27.520 --> 00:18:30.280
Fuck. you're such a gorgeous woman.

319
00:18:30.360 --> 00:18:31.640
[panting]

320
00:18:31.720 --> 00:18:32.720
[flustered]

321
00:18:33.240 --> 00:18:34.400
You've been released.

322
00:18:34.480 --> 00:18:36.040
[Maks mumbling]

323
00:18:36.120 --> 00:18:37.280
Woah. I've got it.

324
00:18:37.360 --> 00:18:38.800
-Ah! Oh. God!
-[Maks groan]

325
00:18:39.680 --> 00:18:40.840
Maks.

326
00:18:42.320 --> 00:18:43.440
Helena...

327
00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:45.240
Maks. get up!

328
00:18:45.520 --> 00:18:47.520
-Grab him. Help him up.
-Gorgeous...

329
00:18:47.600 --> 00:18:48.960
Oh. get up!

330
00:18:49.480 --> 00:18:50.520
Get up!

331
00:18:50.600 --> 00:18:52.200
[struggling efforts]

332
00:18:52.280 --> 00:18:53.320
Helena...

333
00:18:53.400 --> 00:18:55.760
-[struggling efforts]
-Gorgeous...

334
00:18:56.280 --> 00:18:58.400
-Leave him there.
-You're gorgeous.

335
00:18:58.480 --> 00:19:01.080
[panting]

336
00:19:01.160 --> 00:19:02.200
Beautiful.

337
00:19:02.280 --> 00:19:03.840
Stay here and watch him.

338
00:19:04.760 --> 00:19:06.160
But what if he tries to leave?

339
00:19:06.240 --> 00:19:07.320
Don't let him!

340
00:19:17.400 --> 00:19:19.360
CHARITY BALL
FOR CRIPPLED CHILDREN

341
00:19:19.440 --> 00:19:23.320
[singing operatic song]

342
00:19:44.760 --> 00:19:46.520
Thank you for the invitation.

343
00:19:47.760 --> 00:19:50.920
I couldn't pass up
the pleasure of your company.

344
00:19:52.840 --> 00:19:53.800
Please. sit down.

345
00:20:02.160 --> 00:20:04.440
Since this is a charity event.

346
00:20:04.520 --> 00:20:06.360
how about a temporary truce?

347
00:20:06.640 --> 00:20:07.480
[man chuckles]

348
00:20:09.080 --> 00:20:11.240
I'm not at war with you. Helena.

349
00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:16.360
And...

350
00:20:17.400 --> 00:20:19.160
Where's your wife tonight?

351
00:20:20.080 --> 00:20:22.480
Well she's not in prison
like your husband.

352
00:20:24.400 --> 00:20:25.480
She's at home.

353
00:20:25.880 --> 00:20:27.400
-with a migraine.
-Ah.

354
00:20:29.040 --> 00:20:31.760
Then perhaps we seize the opportunity?

355
00:20:34.320 --> 00:20:36.440
To dance! Calm down.

356
00:20:37.080 --> 00:20:40.920
I mean only if God
and the fatherland permit you to.

357
00:20:42.360 --> 00:20:44.400
[people giggling]

358
00:20:44.480 --> 00:20:46.400
It'd be sinful to pass it up.

359
00:20:57.800 --> 00:21:01.000
I wanted to talk to you
about Fortuna's situation.

360
00:21:01.080 --> 00:21:02.560
You mean about Maks's debts?

361
00:21:02.640 --> 00:21:03.480
Mm.

362
00:21:04.120 --> 00:21:05.520
You know about them?

363
00:21:05.600 --> 00:21:08.560
As Fortuna Amandi's next editor-in-chief.

364
00:21:08.640 --> 00:21:10.160
how could I not know?

365
00:21:11.000 --> 00:21:12.000
[Denar chuckles]

366
00:21:16.360 --> 00:21:18.600
The paper will be up for auction.

367
00:21:18.680 --> 00:21:22.080
You'd be a fool if you thought
I'd let that chance slip by.

368
00:21:24.520 --> 00:21:28.480
Makowiecki has promised me
the position of editor-in-chief.

369
00:21:29.760 --> 00:21:31.520
Don't get ahead of yourself.

370
00:21:32.480 --> 00:21:35.600
I know that Fortuna Amandi is your child.

371
00:21:36.080 --> 00:21:37.560
The one you could never have.

372
00:21:37.640 --> 00:21:39.480
-Good night.
-Wait. wait.

373
00:21:44.400 --> 00:21:46.480
The paper will take on a new look.

374
00:21:46.560 --> 00:21:48.680
but I think some things
could stay the same.

375
00:21:48.760 --> 00:21:49.920
wouldn't you say?

376
00:21:51.840 --> 00:21:53.920
We could work together. you and I.

377
00:21:54.960 --> 00:21:56.720
We'd lose the matchmaking

378
00:21:57.480 --> 00:21:58.880
and keep the love.

379
00:21:59.200 --> 00:22:01.040
Be the journalist you are.

380
00:22:02.000 --> 00:22:04.160
You've always been a brilliant writer.

381
00:22:04.680 --> 00:22:06.440
I'm calling the truce off.

382
00:22:07.960 --> 00:22:08.880
[sighs heavily]

383
00:22:17.520 --> 00:22:19.320
[gasp] What're you doing. sir?

384
00:22:19.400 --> 00:22:21.120
-Dear God...
-Something...

385
00:22:21.200 --> 00:22:24.440
[panting] I should have done
a long time ago.

386
00:22:26.520 --> 00:22:28.200
[footsteps receding]

387
00:22:28.280 --> 00:22:30.080
-[applause]
-[violin music playing]

388
00:22:39.600 --> 00:22:40.600
What do you want?

389
00:22:40.680 --> 00:22:41.760
Never enough. is it?

390
00:22:42.240 --> 00:22:43.160
You're drunk. Róża.

391
00:22:43.240 --> 00:22:46.240
My brother. your little lover.
and now Denar too?

392
00:22:47.160 --> 00:22:48.600
Why don't you kiss him already?

393
00:22:48.680 --> 00:22:50.440
-Who?
-Whoever you like.

394
00:22:50.520 --> 00:22:51.800
I'm sick of you!

395
00:22:52.160 --> 00:22:53.480
Leave me alone!

396
00:22:55.120 --> 00:22:56.200
Helena!

397
00:23:03.080 --> 00:23:04.080
Right here.

398
00:23:04.640 --> 00:23:06.280
Can you pull over here?

399
00:23:07.120 --> 00:23:08.680
Let me out. Stop.

400
00:23:13.120 --> 00:23:14.280
Heckmann!

401
00:23:15.640 --> 00:23:16.800
Where is she?

402
00:23:17.280 --> 00:23:18.480
What do you want?

403
00:23:19.920 --> 00:23:21.920
Where is my wife. you bastard?

404
00:23:23.080 --> 00:23:24.240
I have no idea.

405
00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:26.320
-But I find it pretty pathetic...
-Get off!

406
00:23:26.400 --> 00:23:27.680
...that you don't know.

407
00:23:27.760 --> 00:23:28.800
You fucked her.

408
00:23:28.880 --> 00:23:31.160
You did. you lying son of a bitch.

409
00:23:32.880 --> 00:23:36.160
[panting]

410
00:23:40.920 --> 00:23:42.480
[panting continues]

411
00:23:44.080 --> 00:23:45.840
If you can no longer live...

412
00:23:47.600 --> 00:23:49.720
you might as well die. [sobbing]

413
00:23:52.560 --> 00:23:55.320
[both grunting. struggling and panting]

414
00:24:01.400 --> 00:24:02.600
-[Emil grunts]
-[gunshot]

415
00:24:05.680 --> 00:24:06.880
[Róża] He's run off.

416
00:24:07.840 --> 00:24:11.040
He's your brother.
not your damn lover. Christ.

417
00:24:11.120 --> 00:24:13.120
Gonna crawl into his bed as well?

418
00:24:14.160 --> 00:24:15.560
-[scoffs]
-[swallowing]

419
00:24:16.400 --> 00:24:17.600
Wait. come back.

420
00:24:17.680 --> 00:24:19.280
Leave me some opium.

421
00:24:19.680 --> 00:24:20.720
Good night.

422
00:24:21.360 --> 00:24:22.840
I'm leaving him. Róża.

423
00:24:23.720 --> 00:24:26.360
[heavy breathing]

424
00:24:26.440 --> 00:24:27.760
Wiktor Denar...

425
00:24:29.080 --> 00:24:30.920
is a moral authority.

426
00:24:31.000 --> 00:24:34.080
-[chuckles] Oh...
-He's an honorable man.

427
00:24:34.160 --> 00:24:35.880
He would never divorce.

428
00:24:36.400 --> 00:24:38.480
so don't hold your breath for that man.

429
00:24:39.120 --> 00:24:40.560
Forgive me. I'm sorry.

430
00:24:41.360 --> 00:24:43.640
I didn't know you and Denar were a thing.

431
00:24:43.720 --> 00:24:46.120
-[giggles]
-[heavy breathing]

432
00:24:46.200 --> 00:24:47.560
[continues giggling]

433
00:24:47.640 --> 00:24:49.960
You mock me.
but you've never felt passionate love

434
00:24:50.040 --> 00:24:52.720
-and you never will.
-[continues giggling]

435
00:24:52.800 --> 00:24:55.320
You can't imagine
what it would make a woman do

436
00:24:55.400 --> 00:24:56.840
because you aren't brave enough

437
00:24:56.920 --> 00:24:58.920
to feel vulnerability
or passion. you coward.

438
00:24:59.000 --> 00:24:59.960
[giggles] With Denar?

439
00:25:02.680 --> 00:25:04.360
[continues giggling]

440
00:25:08.760 --> 00:25:10.160
[heavy breathing]

441
00:25:10.240 --> 00:25:11.760
[gasping]

442
00:25:11.840 --> 00:25:12.760
Oh...

443
00:25:14.360 --> 00:25:15.720
Take this off.

444
00:25:15.800 --> 00:25:16.760
[whimpering]

445
00:25:20.120 --> 00:25:21.240
Let's go.

446
00:25:34.320 --> 00:25:36.560
Your husband was too drunk to aim.

447
00:25:46.840 --> 00:25:48.480
I think you'd better go.

448
00:25:52.200 --> 00:25:53.240
Want me to?

449
00:26:08.720 --> 00:26:10.760
[Róża] Well I called the doctor and he--

450
00:26:12.920 --> 00:26:14.360
[clearing throat]

451
00:26:16.480 --> 00:26:17.680
Take your lover boy.

452
00:26:17.760 --> 00:26:20.160
pack your things.
and get the fuck out of this house.

453
00:26:20.240 --> 00:26:21.800
Your time's up.

454
00:26:22.480 --> 00:26:23.840
This is my house. Róża!

455
00:26:23.920 --> 00:26:24.760
Helena...

456
00:26:24.840 --> 00:26:26.840
I'll do whatever I want!

457
00:26:28.600 --> 00:26:29.800
Give it!

458
00:26:30.760 --> 00:26:32.040
Screw you.

459
00:26:35.080 --> 00:26:36.720
-[grunts]
-[glass shatters]

460
00:26:42.200 --> 00:26:44.080
[maid] Should I serve breakfast out here?

461
00:26:44.600 --> 00:26:47.440
I'd like you to bring a coffee for me.
sour milk for him.

462
00:26:48.520 --> 00:26:49.360
[Maks scoffs]

463
00:26:50.360 --> 00:26:51.640
[Maks] It says here...

464
00:26:51.720 --> 00:26:55.440
"If women laze about.
intoxicating themselves

465
00:26:55.920 --> 00:26:59.480
with alcohol and opium.
that doesn't bode well

466
00:26:59.560 --> 00:27:01.040
for society."

467
00:27:02.960 --> 00:27:05.440
-[grunting]
-Why did they let you leave?

468
00:27:05.800 --> 00:27:07.040
Janeczek...

469
00:27:07.480 --> 00:27:08.400
[sighs]

470
00:27:09.360 --> 00:27:12.120
...wanted to put me away for murder.

471
00:27:13.400 --> 00:27:15.280
It was a flimsy case.

472
00:27:16.000 --> 00:27:17.880
so they put someone else in charge.

473
00:27:20.080 --> 00:27:23.040
I'm not this Pure-Hearted Jan guy.

474
00:27:25.520 --> 00:27:27.000
As much as I know...

475
00:27:27.720 --> 00:27:29.520
you would like to believe.

476
00:27:31.880 --> 00:27:32.720
[Maks sighs]

477
00:27:37.240 --> 00:27:40.120
-[birds chirping]
-[song playing faintly]

478
00:27:43.160 --> 00:27:44.960
I called the bank of the phone.

479
00:27:45.640 --> 00:27:47.120
They pulled your loan.

480
00:27:48.320 --> 00:27:51.640
It would appear your debts
will bring down our paper.

481
00:27:52.040 --> 00:27:53.280
It's not our paper.

482
00:27:53.360 --> 00:27:54.920
It's my paper.

483
00:27:57.200 --> 00:28:00.400
And I can do
whatever I damn well want with it.

484
00:28:00.680 --> 00:28:02.520
It's Denar's now. actually.

485
00:28:03.240 --> 00:28:05.320
He'll be the next editor-in-chief.

486
00:28:07.000 --> 00:28:08.400
He even offered me a job.

487
00:28:11.720 --> 00:28:14.120
[inhales sharply]
And did you take the job?

488
00:28:19.120 --> 00:28:20.480
[exhales]

489
00:28:24.320 --> 00:28:26.000
You're pathetic. Maks.

490
00:28:30.680 --> 00:28:32.720
[gloomy music playing]

491
00:28:36.360 --> 00:28:38.000
I assume you're here about a loan.

492
00:28:38.080 --> 00:28:40.000
After Denar's attacks.

493
00:28:40.720 --> 00:28:42.000
Mmm...

494
00:28:42.080 --> 00:28:44.240
Fortuna has fallen on hard times.

495
00:28:46.080 --> 00:28:47.000
Mmm...

496
00:28:47.080 --> 00:28:50.280
It's only temporary though.
and with your help we can pull through.

497
00:28:55.920 --> 00:28:58.760
They're trying to take it.
Denar and Makowiecki.

498
00:28:58.840 --> 00:29:01.080
but I won't let them have Fortuna Amandi.

499
00:29:01.480 --> 00:29:02.600
So...

500
00:29:03.840 --> 00:29:05.680
if you become my business partner...

501
00:29:05.760 --> 00:29:06.840
[Ludwik] Mmm.

502
00:29:06.920 --> 00:29:08.240
[puffs]

503
00:29:08.320 --> 00:29:10.200
Can you afford a partnership?

504
00:29:11.000 --> 00:29:11.880
[exhales]

505
00:29:12.720 --> 00:29:14.080
A little birdie told me

506
00:29:14.160 --> 00:29:15.600
the bank pulled all your money.

507
00:29:17.440 --> 00:29:18.440
Simply rumors.

508
00:29:18.520 --> 00:29:20.520
-So. can we count on your help?
-Well...

509
00:29:21.320 --> 00:29:23.440
Mmm. sure. At one time.

510
00:29:25.920 --> 00:29:28.880
But recently. quite a bit of money
disappeared from my safe.

511
00:29:28.960 --> 00:29:30.520
all rather mysteriously.

512
00:29:33.040 --> 00:29:35.280
Care to tell your aunt. my dear.

513
00:29:35.360 --> 00:29:37.360
what you spent all that money on?

514
00:29:41.400 --> 00:29:42.520
[exhales]

515
00:29:48.200 --> 00:29:49.400
[sipping]

516
00:29:50.880 --> 00:29:51.960
I'll leave you alone.

517
00:29:52.720 --> 00:29:55.520
At least tell me
what you spent it on? [clearing throat]

518
00:29:58.480 --> 00:30:00.160
I ended the pregnancy.

519
00:30:02.960 --> 00:30:03.960
[Ludwik clears throat]

520
00:30:09.520 --> 00:30:10.960
What did you just say?

521
00:30:12.280 --> 00:30:15.240
[breathing anxiously]

522
00:30:23.560 --> 00:30:25.240
[continues breathing anxiously]

523
00:30:29.120 --> 00:30:30.440
I got an abortion.

524
00:30:30.880 --> 00:30:31.720
[coughs]

525
00:30:33.560 --> 00:30:35.000
[clears throat]

526
00:30:35.600 --> 00:30:36.720
[clearing throat]

527
00:30:36.800 --> 00:30:38.760
[coughing]

528
00:30:38.840 --> 00:30:41.480
-I aborted your child.
-[clears throat]

529
00:30:41.560 --> 00:30:42.480
I see...

530
00:30:43.120 --> 00:30:44.360
'Cause you raped me.

531
00:30:44.440 --> 00:30:46.120
[inhales and exhales deeply]

532
00:30:46.200 --> 00:30:47.320
You son of a bitch.

533
00:30:47.400 --> 00:30:48.840
[coughing]

534
00:30:48.920 --> 00:30:51.200
[grunts with discomfort]

535
00:30:51.280 --> 00:30:52.320
Do you hear me?

536
00:30:52.400 --> 00:30:53.360
[coughing]

537
00:30:53.440 --> 00:30:54.880
[gasps softly]

538
00:30:54.960 --> 00:30:58.360
-I hope you rot in hell. [growling]
-[clears throat aggressively]

539
00:30:58.440 --> 00:31:00.040
[grunting and panting]

540
00:31:01.000 --> 00:31:01.840
[exhales]

541
00:31:01.920 --> 00:31:02.760
[bell rings]

542
00:31:03.440 --> 00:31:04.400
[grunts]

543
00:31:05.880 --> 00:31:07.280
[inhales and exhales deeply]

544
00:31:07.920 --> 00:31:08.760
[sniffles]

545
00:31:09.280 --> 00:31:12.360
[panting and grunting]

546
00:31:14.840 --> 00:31:16.440
Get out. Both of you.

547
00:31:18.280 --> 00:31:19.240
[exhales]

548
00:31:20.320 --> 00:31:22.360
[clears throat. coughing]

549
00:31:23.200 --> 00:31:24.040
[door opens]

550
00:31:24.560 --> 00:31:25.400
[door closes]

551
00:31:37.560 --> 00:31:38.720
Good evening.

552
00:31:39.120 --> 00:31:42.160
-my dear doctor.
-Ah. Wróblewski!

553
00:31:42.240 --> 00:31:44.680
-I've heard about your troubles.
-Well. my friend.

554
00:31:44.760 --> 00:31:47.400
I've heard about yours as well.

555
00:31:48.600 --> 00:31:50.720
A toast to troublemakers?

556
00:31:50.800 --> 00:31:52.120
The things we do...

557
00:31:53.920 --> 00:31:54.960
for art. huh?

558
00:31:55.040 --> 00:31:56.560
Join me at my table.

559
00:31:56.640 --> 00:31:57.880
Take my cane.

560
00:31:58.400 --> 00:32:00.320
[applause and cheering]

561
00:32:00.400 --> 00:32:02.520
[man 3] Whoo-hoo. Yes!

562
00:32:02.600 --> 00:32:04.760
Excuse me. my table...

563
00:32:06.280 --> 00:32:08.080
I'm sorry sir. but tonight

564
00:32:08.160 --> 00:32:10.120
-you're at another table.
-Mr. Roman...

565
00:32:10.200 --> 00:32:12.240
Right this way. Please follow me. sir.

566
00:32:12.920 --> 00:32:13.760
Come on.

567
00:32:14.840 --> 00:32:16.200
Aren't they wonderful?

568
00:32:16.280 --> 00:32:18.040
-Yes. I could never.
-[chuckle]

569
00:32:18.120 --> 00:32:19.280
Imagine me tap-dancing.

570
00:32:19.360 --> 00:32:21.520
-Mr. Roman...
-[chuckling]

571
00:32:22.000 --> 00:32:23.480
Enjoy the show.

572
00:32:32.720 --> 00:32:34.360
-[man 4] Bravo!
-[people cheering]

573
00:32:34.440 --> 00:32:36.400
-[men] Bravo!
-[man 5] Bravo!

574
00:32:37.000 --> 00:32:38.720
[man 5] More. more!

575
00:32:39.960 --> 00:32:40.880
[actor] My darling.

576
00:32:40.960 --> 00:32:42.600
where in the world have you been?

577
00:32:42.680 --> 00:32:45.800
-At the Conscious Motherhood Clinic.
-[laughing]

578
00:32:45.880 --> 00:32:48.040
Are all those horrible rumors true?

579
00:32:48.120 --> 00:32:50.840
That that place is a den
of sin and indecency?

580
00:32:50.920 --> 00:32:52.280
Of course. my dear husband.

581
00:32:52.360 --> 00:32:54.440
Sinning is kind of par for the course

582
00:32:54.520 --> 00:32:56.840
when so many women in heat
gather in one room.

583
00:32:56.920 --> 00:33:00.000
-[laughing]
-[Makowiecki] That was quite a good one.

584
00:33:00.080 --> 00:33:02.480
[crowd applauding and cheering]

585
00:33:02.560 --> 00:33:04.520
[actor] Thank you. Thank you.

586
00:33:04.600 --> 00:33:06.240
[man 6] Bravo! Bravo!

587
00:33:06.320 --> 00:33:08.240
[knocking]

588
00:33:27.040 --> 00:33:28.480
[breathing heavily]

589
00:33:31.360 --> 00:33:32.720
Emil. I can't do it.

590
00:33:32.800 --> 00:33:34.520
[panting]

591
00:33:34.600 --> 00:33:37.040
I can't go on like this.
[continues panting]

592
00:33:37.120 --> 00:33:38.600
I need my medicine.

593
00:33:39.320 --> 00:33:40.360
Helena!

594
00:33:40.440 --> 00:33:42.520
[continues panting]

595
00:33:42.600 --> 00:33:44.440
You're a doctor. aren't you?

596
00:33:44.520 --> 00:33:45.760
You have to help the sick.

597
00:33:45.840 --> 00:33:48.040
We agreed you wouldn't do this.

598
00:33:48.880 --> 00:33:51.280
[growls] You have to help those in need.

599
00:33:51.360 --> 00:33:53.880
[sobs] Isn't that what you learned
in the academy?

600
00:33:53.960 --> 00:33:56.360
I'm not giving you any drugs.

601
00:33:58.680 --> 00:34:00.680
It's just a little laudanum.

602
00:34:01.320 --> 00:34:03.320
They give it to everyone in the hospital.

603
00:34:03.400 --> 00:34:04.840
Then go to the hospital.

604
00:34:05.920 --> 00:34:07.200
[shuddering]

605
00:34:08.440 --> 00:34:09.520
Helena.

606
00:34:10.800 --> 00:34:11.760
Helena!

607
00:34:12.920 --> 00:34:14.440
-[sighs]
-[door closes]

608
00:34:16.600 --> 00:34:18.600
-[laughing]
-[indistinct chatter]

609
00:34:21.480 --> 00:34:22.960
You damn dirty dog!

610
00:34:23.040 --> 00:34:26.120
-Yeah. woof woof. [laughing]
-[woman laughing]

611
00:34:30.320 --> 00:34:32.800
[Boy] There once was a lovely young thing.

612
00:34:32.880 --> 00:34:35.520
-"My name's Ludmila" I heard her sing.
-[man] Whoo!

613
00:34:35.600 --> 00:34:38.560
-[woman] Oh.
-Though I admit she was a little fat.

614
00:34:38.960 --> 00:34:41.040
-She was always...
-[woman laughing]

615
00:34:41.120 --> 00:34:43.199
-...rather keen to chat!
-[Maks] Keen to chat!

616
00:34:43.280 --> 00:34:44.120
[laughing]

617
00:34:44.199 --> 00:34:46.280
[cheering]

618
00:34:49.480 --> 00:34:51.960
-[laughing]
-[Boy] She would often dream at night.

619
00:34:52.040 --> 00:34:55.280
-that a noble knight would...
-[Maks] Bang her! [laughing]

620
00:34:55.360 --> 00:34:58.280
...take her in his might. And she...

621
00:34:58.360 --> 00:35:02.120
with eager delight.
would offer her virtue outright.

622
00:35:02.200 --> 00:35:04.400
and she was quite fond of him.

623
00:35:04.920 --> 00:35:06.640
She'd give her body.

624
00:35:06.720 --> 00:35:08.960
Who cares it wasn't slim?

625
00:35:09.040 --> 00:35:10.360
-[Boy] Cheers!
-[Maks] Whoo!

626
00:35:10.440 --> 00:35:11.600
[laughing]

627
00:35:11.680 --> 00:35:13.040
[Maks] Darling!

628
00:35:13.960 --> 00:35:17.800
Everyone look!
Dear guests. it's my darling wife

629
00:35:17.880 --> 00:35:20.400
who's just come back from her lover.

630
00:35:21.920 --> 00:35:24.600
Well. how about it?
Wanna join us. sweetheart?

631
00:35:26.040 --> 00:35:28.280
-[woman chuckles]
-[man 7] Cheers!

632
00:35:28.360 --> 00:35:31.280
[laughing]

633
00:35:35.920 --> 00:35:39.120
-To the innocence of youth!
-[cheering]

634
00:35:39.200 --> 00:35:41.160
[woman] Whoo! Cheers!

635
00:35:41.520 --> 00:35:43.120
Vodka. vodka. vodka. vodka.

636
00:35:43.200 --> 00:35:44.600
[exclaims]

637
00:35:50.680 --> 00:35:52.760
[muffled party in the distance]

638
00:35:59.800 --> 00:36:01.120
Here. this will help.

639
00:36:11.080 --> 00:36:12.160
[grunts softly]

640
00:36:20.400 --> 00:36:21.720
Mom. I. um...

641
00:36:24.160 --> 00:36:25.880
When you were a baby...

642
00:36:28.400 --> 00:36:30.400
you refused to take my breast.

643
00:36:32.160 --> 00:36:33.680
As if to punish me.

644
00:36:33.760 --> 00:36:36.280
Mom... Mom. I'm... [whimpers]

645
00:36:37.120 --> 00:36:39.720
[sniffles] I would never do it on purpose.

646
00:36:41.840 --> 00:36:43.680
You're the same as your father.

647
00:36:47.400 --> 00:36:48.240
[Róża exhales]

648
00:36:49.080 --> 00:36:51.320
You were always so stubborn.

649
00:36:51.400 --> 00:36:53.120
It was hard to love you.

650
00:37:11.840 --> 00:37:14.240
-Why must you put me through--
-Oh. hush you.

651
00:37:18.880 --> 00:37:20.640
I have to help Helena.

652
00:37:34.920 --> 00:37:37.400
I'm sorry for what I said. I was terrible.

653
00:37:38.920 --> 00:37:40.480
And thank you again.

654
00:37:41.160 --> 00:37:42.560
Don't mention it.

655
00:37:43.320 --> 00:37:45.240
After all. we're sisters.

656
00:37:47.440 --> 00:37:50.640
There's nothing that can't be forgiven
when it comes to family.

657
00:37:51.320 --> 00:37:52.240
[blows sharply]

658
00:37:53.240 --> 00:37:55.000
Tell that to your daughter.

659
00:37:56.680 --> 00:37:58.400
She needs to hear it.

660
00:37:59.200 --> 00:38:01.480
Ewa has to join the real world.

661
00:38:01.560 --> 00:38:04.920
And the real world forces you to learn
from your mistakes.

662
00:38:06.720 --> 00:38:07.760
And you?

663
00:38:10.640 --> 00:38:12.000
What did you learn?

664
00:38:17.200 --> 00:38:18.600
I learned to forgive.

665
00:38:38.440 --> 00:38:39.840
I forgive you.

666
00:38:41.400 --> 00:38:43.480
[tense music playing]

667
00:38:46.240 --> 00:38:47.880
[exhales]

668
00:39:12.800 --> 00:39:13.840
[gasps softly]

669
00:39:23.280 --> 00:39:25.240
[sinister music playing]

670
00:39:25.320 --> 00:39:26.480
[Ewa] Helena!

671
00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:30.960
Mom?

672
00:39:31.440 --> 00:39:32.440
Helena!

673
00:39:32.840 --> 00:39:33.720
[Róża screams]

674
00:39:33.800 --> 00:39:35.960
[panting]

675
00:39:36.040 --> 00:39:37.680
[Róża] Oh. my god. I just found her.

676
00:39:37.760 --> 00:39:39.320
[panting]

677
00:39:44.600 --> 00:39:47.160
[Ewa] Can you hear me. Helena?
[shuddering breaths]

678
00:39:47.240 --> 00:39:48.640
Come on. Wake up!

679
00:39:49.040 --> 00:39:51.760
-Helena. wake up. please!
-It's over. darling. She's dead.

679
00:39:52.305 --> 00:40:52.315
Do you want subtitles for any video?
